column25: Comments
Very fast and efficient with its time usage, was able to quickly remove algae before scoring, had a very fast found intake.
Lost track of it in part of teleop. Very fast cycle times and precise auto align. Very quick climb.
Can work on both algae and coral, all level and high accuracy, also get and hold coral quick and tight
I missed half the match, but from what I observed they are a very basic robot. Slow cycle times, takes some time to aim, pretty accurate most of the time when scoring
Its elevator got stuck? right after auto they went to collect coral from the station. but when it attempted to move its elevator up. the coral got stuck in the bottom.
Somewhat slow, but very inaccurate
Never missed, atempted to move algae but moved it to the upper pegs instead

Looked like they attempted to climb at 10 seconds left, but they were not fruitful. Their drivebase has the smoothest control I’ve seen; they auto align with high precision. Fast on all levels and no wasted movement.
Get the coral fast and tight, can work on the level over 1 but need more time to aiming during level 3
Their autos missed every time they tried to get algae. Cycle times are smooth and quick, very reliable for ground intake and scoring. Is able to fill up a good chunk of the reef
Very Accurate, no other comments
Highly accurate, but had a poor auto. Very unique climb mechanism
Very consistent algae scoring and had great accuracy when scoring coral

Did not attempt to climb; slow cycle times; ran into partners twice; has scoring capabilities on all levels; did not attempt to even leave in auto; did not attempt to climb; possibly inexperienced operator (sent elevator up once when it wasn’t supposed to); no auto alignment on reef so it takes a wh
Only 1 miss during Level 4, aiming fast and have higher accuracy
Very good auto and accuracy! Cycle time could use some improvement, but is overall a reliable robot for scoring. Intakes pretty well from station
It got coral stuck in it, and TRIED to do defense. but just did not move.
Kind of slow, but accurate on L1 and L2
Had a very consistent ground intake, could accurately score on L2-4 and had very fast cycle times
Small, moderately slow robot; quick climb; scored 2 algae (not counted in my totals) into the opponent’s processor to achieve coopertition
Trying to stop other robot getting coral, catch the good time (sometimes) Failed on L4 , didn’t aiming well
Autos are a bit slow, but very good. Pretty good for barge and L4 scoring, though their cycle times are a little on the slower side. Is also reliable for removing algae from reef
Tried to intake several times, gave up and switched to defense. Towards the end got beached on an algae. Auto is not accurate because wasn’t watching.
End effector roo wobbly during auto to score, but is able to pick coral up off the floor
Very consistent when scoring on L4 but far less effective on L2 either accidentally scoring in L1 or shooting the coral so hard it bounced out

Algae bot with net and processor capabilities;  could have climbed if it wasn’t resting on coral; algae bounced out of net twice and they pushed algae off the field once; the other team had an algae bot too so they could’ve scored more if there was not competition for algae
Work on coral on Level 1-3, miss more on L3 and 1, aiming fast about 60% accuracy

Autos are.. strange.. sent a coral flying?? Can manipulate coral amd algae at the same time. Sometimes struggled with coral and algae, but is generally pretty accurate. Somewhat slow cycle times, they waste quite a bit of time trying to ground intake both coral and algae
Not too fast speeds between coral station and reef but was very accurate when attempting. It tried to score algae in the net in auto but missed
Somewhat accurate, no auto, but very fast
Fairly slow compared to others but was consistent in scoring on L3

Algae net bot that can only intake algae directly from the reef; attempted and failed to score in net 3 times; incurred a minor foul for touching the net; slow movement; not able to climb - parked with 20 sec left because no algae was left on the reef to intake
Working well during auto time, can work on level 2-4, miss 2 on Level 4

Slowly inches out of starting zone during auto, nothing else. Almost got stuck on algae and coral, then got fully stuck on algae.. but freed themselves! Had a specific vendetta against 10073, was keeping them from getting to coral station
had a ground intake and could score really fast and could easily score on every level
Can score both coral and algae, but much better with algae than coral
Missed a lot of scoring
Could score anything. Has very good ground intake. Missed a lot of l4 tries but could get almost everything usually.
very effective bot that can score and ground intake very effectively. missed very few pieces on scoring and none on intake.
Was slow at outtaking to L2

Tje robot moved slowly between the reef and the coral station during auto. Auto was meant to be two coral and ended at the coral station. Can intake from ground. Missed intake from coral station two times. Missed scoring on reef 2 times, L1 and L3. The robot started doing defense with 45 seconds lef
They had a good coral score wherever they wanted to go
Missed all shots in auto and very fast cycle time in tele
Only missed one shot (L4) and could remove algae very quickly. Also is very stable and will not be pushed around easily.
drove into L4 position in auto but dropped coral and didnt attempt to score. missed one L4 in teleop .
Fast intake, auto missed first and third coral. Driving was weird and in arcs, stood by the cage for the last 1:30
The robot’s auto was quick and it was almost three coral. Sometimes the robot paused before lifting the elevator or running the end effector when trying to score L4. L3 and L2 were much smoother.
They tried for 7 algae’s in the net made 5 smile and clean L1
Knocked off algae for teammate and intook coral very fast
DO NOT PICK THIS ROBOT! It only picks algae off ground and scores in procesor. Also has lots of difficulty picking up algae.
3.5 coral auto robot made it half way to coral station. removed 2 algae. very fast cycle and ran out of time to climb.
Very fast and accurate intake and outtake, fast climb. Tippy at full extension
The coral travels throughout the robot to the end effector so it doesn’t have to turn around to score in the reef, makes circles quicker. Had to take out coral and reintake it two times.
They had 100 percent accuracy in the net but struggled with coral accuracy
Ground intake, super fast cycle time and didn’t miss any scoring attempts
Very accurate and consistent and fast, good at algae net scoring too. (It’s cpr, what did you expect)
3 coral auto failed. very fast scoring and super accurate in teleop.
Slow at outtaking, tippy, can’t climb, good reef alignment.
Missed scoring in reef 2 times. Auto removed an algae and then went and bumped into driver station wall. Algae removal was very funky.
They got every algae they tried for, ok but L1
Something broke so started defense and missed any shots it took and moved around field slow
Missed many lower level shots but was consistent up top. Can remove algae well.

moved to coral sttion after 2 coral auto. dropped one coral in transit after being caught on lgae. removed 2 algae. tried to score in the same spot once and missed. starting stumbling around during end game. did not attempt climb
Ground intake, slow outtake, didn’t go to park.
Sometimes the end effector bumped against the algae when the elevator lifted. An algae was removed but I think the coral was the thing that removed it.
They had good touch it own it with 100 percent accuracy in coral and algae
Carried a algae with them while scoring coral and missed a net shot
ground and source intake fairly consistent at lower levels, but at higher levels, very wobbly and not as accurate. also ground intake took a while
failed 3 coral. got stuck on algae needed help getting unstuck. did not attempt climb. struggled to intake and very slow cycle.
Slow driving, dropped  coral once, not enough time to climb.
Removed algae two times in teleop. Pretty fast removal. Cycles were fast and without interruption.
Great intaking speed with fantastic aim and was able to easily help unstick a robot

2.5 coral auto (scored 2, got coral, and made it back to reef); focused on L1 to get coral RP because other bots were slow at L1; quick, consistent scoring on all levels; helped get alliance member unstuck from algae; fast cycle times and never missed an intake
Can work on both algae and coral, have high accuracy and aiming fast. Get coral smoothly

A little bit tipsy, struggled to intake from station. Defense was okay, but struggled to have much of an effect because they drive slower than the robots they are blocking. Overall, not super reliable of offense nor defense
auto is very aggressive, and driving is very aggressive at times. Good ground intake
Very accurate, but knocked it's own coral off of the reef
Was able to quickly score coral and then remove and score the algae on the reef
Very consistent
Trying to stop other robot getting coral, but it not heavy enough(I guess)to really affect them. Incurred 2x minor fouls.

Cycle time is pretty smooth and quick, but could use some improvement on speed and accuracy due to the fact they missed quite a few times while scoring. Took a bit of time to aim, still a good robot. Attempted L4 in auto and coral landed in L1 by mistake. Attempted a 2nd L4 but it was misaligned and they A-stopped very tactfully.
2 times shot out coral from back, very good ground intake
Very slow, and very unstable
Was able to quickly score almost all the algae but was only able to score on L1
Intake failed often but very consistent L4 scoring. Robot got pushed around easily
Working well in auto, have higher accuracy, can pick the corals on the ground so it’s not affected by defense
Cycle time is smooth and speedy, very reliable for scoring, can manipulate both coral and algae and does it well. Very reliable for filling reef
Great ground intake, and also just good robot in general
Decent defense, but very inaccurate
Was able to efficiently score coral and algae resulting in very fast scoring across the match
Can work on all levels of coral, have higher accuracy, aiming fast and smooth
Very slow scoring can score L4 but usually got there too slow
Slow cycle times, ran into cages at full speed? Wastes a lot of time trying to intake from station, and are a little bit slow
At the beginning it dejected coral, but only happened once, can do l1 but missing more than it hit
Accurate, but only on L1 and L2, failed climb
Was able to score on L2-4 but occasionally missed on the lower levels was also able to clear the reef of algae
Often went for lower coral when higher coral were available  Fast and consistent outtake and intake and fast scoring
Can hold algae, but have trouble on put it in net. Can’t hold coral well when it is working on lower level (sometimes). Be able to do level 4
Slow cycle times, waste a lot of time driving around because they don't move very quickly. Reliable for L3 scoring and possibly removing algae from reef (only saw once)
When lining up to put down coral very slow, when collecting coral. they don’t need to line up really. Hesitate when putting coral on the reef.
Had some trouble during auto aiming, and keeping balance
Was able to score on all 4 levels but had some acuracy problems with coral specifically
Very slow and wobbly outtake didn’t line up well on L4
an algae bot, takes a bit of time to pick it up. got in the way of its own teammates.
Not strong enough to stop other robot getting coral
Good speedy cycle times, very accurate with scoring, very little issues with intaking. Overall a very balanced robot
Can score accurately and efficiently in al levels
Moved around field slow, and had ground and normal coral intake
Ours

dropped one in auto. dropped one in teleop. removed 1 algae. missed one and it dropped to L1. took 20 secs to climb. overall pretty fast but somewhat innacurrate. was on top of an algae while climbing.
Very fast ground intake, outtake, and climb. Can do algae in net and processor with 100% accuracy
Really fast coral score. Can very consistently do score algea in net and coral. Ground intake
The scoring took along time but they did make it in for all of the coral
Fast cycle time and broke for few seconds at start of the match
Has trouble picking up algae but very good scorer and consistent with L1 but can’t score anything higher on reef
removed an algae in auto. didnt attempt to score more than once. stole algae from other side. missed 2 algae in teleop. very good cycle.
Very fast intake and outtake, missed handoff once.
Tried scoring algea in net but it bounced out. Auto was supposed to be more but it didn’t intake coral. Slow cycles. Missed one time.
They had ok algae
Tried to climb but couldn’t, and moved slow around field
Took a long time to line up to reef but very consistent and can score anything level
2.5 coral auto. removed 2 alge. missed 1 coral in L1. super fast cylce and near perfect accuraccy.
Very fast and accurate. Fast algae
Their auto removed an algea and was supposed to score coral, but the robot overshot and bumped into the reef and tipped a little. It was very tippy throughout the match.
Served as bad defense
Had trouble trying to align coral when scoring
Missed L1 and L4 many times but mostly just looked broken like it couldn’t outtake so it didn’t do anything all match.
2.5 coral auto. almost fell over with elevator. missed 1 L3. good cycle and near perfect accuraccy. no attempt to climb
Almost climbed. Missed one algae in auto.
Removed algea one time during auto. Auto ended with a coral in the robot near the coral station. Fast cycles. Missed outtake of coral one time.
They have an accurate coral on L1 L2 L3
Something broke in the robot so they went to go play defense
Didn’t miss a single shot and had very fast cycle times, took no time to line up and can remove algae but not score it.
auto crashed into driver stations. missed L4. removed an algae. inconsistent ground intake but mostly consistent scoring and source intake as fallback.
Coral got stuck in handoff. Fast and efficient. Data may be inacurate
Focused on lower levels. Auto was fine
The coral was good algae was ok
Didn’t miss and shots and had fast cycle times
Very accurate and consistent but slow elevator speed and slow drive speed.
did not attempt 2 coral autos. ws frozen at the start of teleop untill 1:45. Even so good cycle and accuracy.
Fast, removed algae using coral tho, climb was slightly too low
Very unstable, tippy, and slow intake. Feels like the intake and end effector are about to fall of.
They were a bad defense bit
Able to consistently remove and score algae in the net and was able to quickly and effectively score on all levels
Doing well in auto, can work on both corals and algae. Have high accuracy and work smoothly
Good cycle time speed, amazing accuracy, reliable for scoring on all 4 levels, was stuck on an algae for a little bit
auto started late, and when auto was over took a good 10 seconds to start up again.
Can score both coral and algae, good at both
Was able to score on most levels perfectly fine could clear and score algae as well
Robot only scored algae but was very accurate at removing it from reef and putting it in net
Working well but takes some time on getting coral. Lose connection in seconds before it end
just at the beginning the head of the elevator got stuck, but only for a quick moment. Other than that a very good robot
Had stability issues, and lowered accuracy
Was able to score on most levels pretty accurately by did struggle some, was also able to quickly clear algae as it went back to coral station
Robot had a solid intake but a very wobbly outtake that made it hard to align  Climb was very fast and took 6 seconds to align and ascend
Working on level 1-3, didn’t try level 4 or not be able to try. Miss 2 in level 3.
Struggles to intake from coral station, somewhat slow cycle time, but they make up for it with their reliable L4 scoring. Defense was.. okay..
Could not find my robot during their auto, I estimated their auto. At first the cycles were slow but eventually they became very consistent and fast. Removed algea two times and scored both of them.
Very fast, but somewhat inaccurate. Failed to climb
Could not score in auto and attempted to play defense but then got stuck on an algae
My form restarted in the middle of the match but from what the team did well they were consistent when scoring algae
Doing well in auto. Lose connection for a while, fixed it 15 seconds before end, accuracy get down (might because the pressure from time)
Good cycle time, smooth scoring, reliable for L3 and L4 scoring as well as met scoring. Got a coral stuck in their robot and did not notice.
Auto was nice. Cycles got interrupted and were not quick. Tried scoring L1 two times, failed both times.
Very fast, somewhat accurate, poor auto, failed climb
Able to score on all levels, had a very slow auto w/ a ground intake
Robot was consistent in intake and outtake but was very wobbly and almost fell down while driving
Not strong and fast enough to stop other robots, can work on algae but takes time on catching and holding it.
Accuracy with scoring and intaking is amazing, good cycle time, reliable for removing algae and scoring on all of the levels. Overall, well balanced robot.
Tried scoring coral one time on L1 reef throughout teleop, missed. Took a long time to collect algea and score it.
Very slow, end effector and elevator are shaky
Able to quickly score on all levels but had a poor auto
Very fast and consistent algae scoring but can only score l1 coral
Aiming and getting corals fastly, but miss a lot (especially Level 3). Doing fine in auto
Good cycle time, very reliable for algae scoring, constantly needs to have algae on the ground in order to score
Chased algea around the field. Not very effective. Got distracted for a few seconds so my data might be missing something.
Very accurate, fast, poor auto
Very effective coral intake, and fast cycle time
Missed many L4 shots because of wellness and has slow cycle times but can despite algae and score on all levels.
did not attempt to score in auto. removed 4 algae.very slow cycle but accurate. got stuck on algae and couldnt park.
Fast ground intake and coral placement. Can score algae in net and processor, fast climb. Potential object detection in autos
Ground intake for coral; can score algae in net and processor but can’t clear algae from the reef; missed an L3 once, but it seemed to be an operator error rather than an auto align error.
They had solid accuracy on Al 4 levels of coral simple auto
Tried to climb but failed, had ground intake and normal intake
Very consistent with good aim. Fast cycle times with ground intake too.
removed 1 algae in teleop and one in auto. played as defense bot very well foe half the match.  good cycle. no missed shots .
Struggled to accurately intake, kept missing coral placement on reef. Was unable to line up climb so they went or score one last algae instead.
No auto alignment in reef, so takes a while to outtake. Very solid net scoring and algae temoval
They had all 4 levels but were moving to quickly and kept missing
Missed a coral in auto, took a while to intake coral, missed a barge shot
Auto can score 3 coral but missed 2, very accurate with very fast cycle times, can do any type of scoring, has ground and station intake.
removed 3 alge in teleop. cycle so fast its hard to keep track.
Attempted 3 coral but only made 2; fast cycle times; missed L2 twice because a coral was blocking the reef and they didn’t see it.
Stopped moving for a sec near end of the match and had fast cycle time
No coral, only can score algae and defend. Also has slow algae cycle times.
removed 3 algae during teleop. ground intake gsve it an ultra fast cycle along with perfect accuracy.
Very fast cycle time with both direct from coral station and ground intake

Very quick algae acquisition from ground and reef, touch & own it ground coral, consistant l1 scoring. Can score in net & processor, but slows to approach net, presumably so as not to tip over or hit the net. Algae removal in auto.
They go all levels and made all shoots attempted
Tried to score 2 algae in auto but missed and ground intake
Only scores algae in processor with a 1 L1 coral auto. Has trouble picking up algae and bobbles it a lot. Very OK cycle times.
failed 3 coral auto. got defended. missed some shots and didnt handle being defende well. did not attempt climb
Robot was disabled about a minute in but was still very slow while it was active

Fairly effective defense; was moving between the 2 stations to disrupt, hit at stretegic times to mess with intaking, moved game pieces towards the station they weren’t at to create obstructions. Didn’t shut them down, but slowed them down. NO PENALTIES
They could do all levels ok, just were moving at bit fast and missed some
Got stuck twice on a algae, tried to remove the algae but couldn’t
MISSED WAY TOO MANY. Has medium cycle times without any consistency, can only score coral, and is quite wobbley.
helped friend get unstuck on algae. near flawless intake and flawless outtake. did not attempt to park. did not attempt 3 coral auto.
Was able to grab algae from everywhere and score it extremely fast, would have scored more but the algae kept bouncing out because the barge was too full
Fairly quick intake, but slow line up w reef. Arm wiggled when they moved, slowed down alignment. Very quick ground intake. Attempted 1 L4 auto, missed
Very good all on all levels, quick cycles. No algae
Had very fast cycle times and could effectively score algae, did have some problems with accuracy at the start when attempting on the lower levels
Slow cycle time and coral can bounce off the intake and go through the robot
Have high accuracy, can get points stable.
Speedy cycle times along with great accuracy, scoring speed, and versatility with scoring. Very balanced robot
Coral station intake, can reach all levels on the reef and can very easily take algae off the reef but a lot of the time bounces out of the net when attempted (shot 3 algae made one of them)
Can accurately score in levels between L1 and L3, but has balance issues due to elevators tilt. Elevator swaying can add momentum to coral causing it to miss.
Had issues with there had off forcing them to play defense, defense could have been better due to the other team having ground intakes allowing them to cover the field with coral to pick up
Elevator swaying can add momentum to coral causing it to miss
On level 1, got 2/3 miss. Did not climb successfully. Used center auto.

Tried to score L4 and failed the first time. Slight issue with almost tipping ovet. The only reason I bumped them down from very effective is due to their struggles to get coral onto the reef several times at the beginning and once more towards the end. Small issue with almost getting stuck on algae
did a little of coral but most of the time just messed around with algae. and went to the other side of the field and scored 2 in the wrong processor?
Incredibly fast, very smooth intake, the best auto I have seen so far
Very efficient algae removal and had a good cycle time
Lighter and easier to punch around
Doing well in auto. Can work on both algae and corals, but couldn’t hold algae really well. Aiming fast but accuracy is not high
Their defense skills are.. eehhh.. didn't really do that much to help their team and their defense hardly affected anything on the other alliances side of the field. Overall, not the best
had a ground intake which took a while cycle through, and it was very wobbly when it was fully extended was fairly accurate but took a long time to lineup
So incredibly fast, incredibly accurate, nearly perfect auto, nearly instant climb
Had slow movement and had some difficulties holding onto coral when it had it.
Coral fell out of end effector and James elevator. Tried to place coral on a place talready had coral
Mostly working on algae. Can also working on corals, but mostly lower level ( like level 1)

Autosmissed the first time, scored other two pieces. Very versatile in terms of scoring, although they missed a couple times. Very reliable for quick points in every method. Also has a unique ability of shoot coral out when it grabs too many at once, very cool!
could score on all levels however you did not go to the highest level because it would be very wobbly. average cycle time
Good auto, can score accurately in all levels, but somewhat slow
Had great cycle times and was able to use wheels on intake to remove algae and well as pick it off the ground
Robot can hold one coral and one algae at the same time to score in the processor and on the reef with in ten seconds of each other
Can work on level 2-4, have high accuracy but use more time on aiming
Very reliable for L2, 3 and 4 but struggle to score L1. Not super fast, but cycle times are still relatively quick and very smooth. Very balanced robot, reliable for filling the reef up
intake at the source good score on every level fairly fast cycle time, solid robot all around
Very fast, but not very accurate. End effector can pivot in 3 different directions, and can hold coral and algae at the same time, while scoring both
Had a 3 coral auto and enough time to grab another coral, was also very fast and accurate with ability to score everywhere
Very light easy to throw around, intake can get jammed.
Move fast, can work on both corals and algae and have high accuracy . Takes more time on getting corals
Removes algae and scores 1 coral in auto. Somehow managed to score L1 a few times even though they were dropping them from high up, but it's not reliable. Not reliable for scoring nor defense
Algae removal was fast and directly deposited in net
Kind of slow. Got foul because they held 2 coral. Coral got jammed in intake for rest of match
Ground intake and got a coral stuck in their end effector for a sec twice
Has trouble picking up algae but has ground and reef intake for algae and only ground and L1 for coral. Can only score coral in L1. Has algae auto. Sometimes controls algae and coral at once.
did not attempt to score in auto. got defended but handled it well. never missed.

One coral auto missed by a lot. Wobby takes a lot of time to align to L4 occasionally. Prettyy good deep climb. Fast acceleration but slow top speed, about average for navigation, drivers appear to be in sync somewhat, no major issues apparent.
Robot only left. Then went straight to defense. They were being worked on on the field prior to the match. Had a coral stuck in them while on defenses
They were able to score on all 4 levels, had deep climb and algae removal and net score, they were accurate with all moves
Very fast climb and very fast cycle time with ground intake
Missed a few but overall made most tries and can score algae in net and processor. Fast cycles and good 2 coral auto.
did not attempt 2 coral. removed 2 algae in teleop. got efended but handled it well. did not miss and had a good cycle.
Very fast cycles, but they did miss a few times. Like 4-5 or so.
Deliveredd o the processor and played defense.  Was stuck on an algae for 45 seconds
They had insanely fast cycle time and had smooth moves, made all shoots attempted lol 4 levels and algae removal, fast deep climb
Climbs at 15 seconds left and fast cycle time
No show
failed 3 coral. removed an algae in teleop. good cycle but started missing more.

Solid auto. Fast Algae removal. Robot is average speed, with fast acceleration. The drivers appear to have some communication problems as the robot seemed conflicted at times. A coral got wedged in part of the intake, and they had to ram the robot to get it out. Overall not bad.
Attempted 2 L1 without success. Slow line up on climb but accurate when hooked.
They can score on all 4 levels but still miss some, they can climb
Fact cycle time and worked well around teammates by not being in their way at all
Very wobbly but can score algae in processor and net and score coral on all levels with OK cycle times.
missed an L4 in teleop. missed 2  intakes. 3.5 coral auto. removed an algae. fast cycle.

3 coral auto, missed 2. Deep climb failed. Missed a lot. Fast robot. Beginning was rough, but fell into a groove. Coral missed while intaking and while scoring many times. Drivers appeared to make cohesive decisions, just a rough robot.
Slow delivery, decent ground intake
They were moving very quickly and not making very many although they did have fast cycle time
Their ground intake broke halfway though match so tried to do normal intake hit didn’t work
VERY inaccurate, took about 15 shots and only scored 4. Can score all levels with good cycle times but accuracy is just not there.
ran out of time to deepclimb.  very fast cycle and very good accuraccy.

Solid 1 coral auto. Beautiful algae removal, scores pieces while removing algae. Effective ground intake cleans up the ground. Coral is moved smoothly through the bot. Drivers worked well together; however, it was ultimately conflicted about what to do. Missed twice when trying to score in L1.
Attempted a net and missed. Added algae to other processor.
They were able to move smoothly fast cycles
Failed to remove an algae once, missed 2 coral shots
Kit bot with shallow climb. Can only score L1 and algae in processor. Big and strong so can do decent defense.
failed 3 coral auto. removed 3 algae in teleop. dropped one L3. no attempt to climb. super fast cycle and near perfect
Auto drove forward, coral fell out of robot once. Driver seemed to be a bit confused on what to to/ where to go.
Fast and accurate cycles.
They were able to score on alll levels and could do algae but were not good at anything to be a solid choice
Never missed a shot and had very fast cycles, however they had a nonfunctional auto
Fast intake and scoring, struggled to get algae off
Mostly working on algae, might be able to work on coral, but only low level. Have some problems on one side wheel (I guess) couldn’t move smoothly at seconds before the end
Average. Don't know if they can climb, kept cycling algae
Could not tell if it was trying to do defense or collect algae. very finicky, took a long time to collect algae and was just running around for a part of it
able to remove algae very fast, but not doing anything with it. cycle time is very fast able to move coral quickly
Had a nonfuctioning auto that missed to coral, had slower movements and cycles
Fast ground intake. Reliable algae removal and scoring.
Have high accuracy and move fast. Takes time on climbing but success
Kept cycling coral instead of climbing, can they?
Very slow, could not intake coral well. and when trying to put it on the reef it was not at all effective.
Somewhat slow, had a hard time lining up end effector to score, and get coral from source
Had a 3 coral auto but only on L3, relatively fast cycles but I am unsure if they can reach L4
Fast ground intake. Fast climb. Fast algae net scoring

Doing well in auto. Can work on both algae and coral. It might have problems on its arm, not I am not sure is that a miss or a problem (couldn’t take coral high enough to reach level 4) takes time on climbing but success
Algae removal from reef and ground. Good delivery to processor and net.
very fast cycle times, very fast robot.
Very accurate, but unstable. Got a foul from popping an algae
Had very slow movement missed its one coral in auto and missed most shots at L4
Missed first coral in auto. Climb was very low and a bit slow.
Might be able to do better in auto. Aiming fast and high accuracy, climbing fast.
Slow robot,  processor work on both sides put two in opposing alliance processor
very slow elevator, can barely move alger, auto moves slow. can barely score above l1
Somewhat slow, had coral fall out of end effector multiple times

Used wood before match to align the robot parallel with rhe reef, had a interesting intake that could simultaneously grab algae and score coral while also being able to pick up off the ground, had slight problems with coral retention
Fast and easy in taking from coral station with funnel, but can’t intake when coral is in between the coral station wall. Auto missed two coral on l4 because it was outtaking too fast.
Takes time on aiming but have higher accuracy. Can pick the coral on the ground, but sometimes couldn’t hold it really well.
Great robot. Was a slow ish and work coral late missed the climb due to time.
algae kept falling out of robot, very frount heavy,
Very slow, very unstable, very inaccurate, had coral fall out of I take multiple times
Would have had faster intaking but hard problems with a handoff
Good net algae scoring, ran into coral station causing robot to disable for a few seconds. Auto was a bit slow.
Can work on both algae and coral. Can pick up the corals on the ground and have higher accuracy. Move really fast and aiming fast, too.
Great match to watch!!!!  There robot was browning out before the climb.
very fast, sometimes missed net but other than that very accurate. really good robot
Very fast and accurate, can score algae in net, but auto has some issues
Tried to score in auto but it didn’t work
It only missed one. But has a 1 L4 coral auto. Has decent cycle time but is VERY consistent. Also has the ability to do any algae scoring.
failed 3 coral. missed 2 in teleop L4. removed one algae. very fast cycle and mostly accurate with perfect intake.
Determined
They were able to score on all levels, they had quick alignment with the ref, did not have algae but did climb quickly
Auto knocked two algae that are balanced on coral, scored L4 and knocked off an algae. Cycle time kinda slow. Missed outtakint on reef once.
